      <h2><a class="anchor" id="top" name="brownies"></a>The 3rd Sanderstead Brownies</h2>
      <p>The Rainbows and Brownies of the 3rd Sanderstead are going to have to close down this coming July after being a successful pack for over 90 yeaes if they are unable to find a new leader.</p>
      <p>Glenys Baker, after 18 years, has decided it is time to retire and will be leaving the 3rd this coming July. Sadly two of her longstanding helpers have also said they will be standing down.</p>
      <p>The pack are currently 26 in number. For their first 88 years they were based at St Mary's Church Hall, but like a number of other organisations had to recently find alternative premises and were fortunate to find a home with the United Reformed Church on Sanderstead Hill.</p>
      <p>The 3rd have an active programme leading up to the summer with a sleepover on HMS Belfast on the Thames and a camp in Cobham. Glenys has devoted 18 years to the 3rd and has earned the thanks of the current and so many former Brownies for her energy and enthusiasm in leading the pack forward.</p>
      <p>It is now time for others to step forward, a project for friends.</p>
        
